nd ensure expenses are coded accurately by department and team(s) to facilitate timely budget versus actual spend Manage the budget process by working cross functionally with department heads to examine current costs, changes, and any necessary cuts or additions to the budget Own the Asset and Liability portion of Balance Sheet from a reconcilement and activity perspective Safeguard company assets and acts with the highest diligence and care when paying vendors and employees in both USD and cryptocurrencies Provide management with timely and accurate information that is vital to making data-driven decisions Assess current accounting operations, offer recommendations for improvement and implement new processes to increase efficiency or accuracy when needed Maintain database oversight of negotiated contracts and ensure vendors are paid per contractual obligations and in accordance with schedules, as well as reconciling prepaid and general accrual accounts Lead employee trainings on payroll procedures and relevant regulations Update payroll system to reflect employee crypto payment elections Maintain immaculate records and acts with the highest integrity Protect assets by establishing, monitoring, and enforcing internal controls Assist the Controller and CFO with audits and related activity Success Metrics of Position Completion of monthly financial statement reports for all stakeholders by agreed upon deadline All vendor bills are accounted for systematically, within budget, and paid on time Vendors are paid per invoice terms Adherence to proper approvals in accordance with company-wide approval matrix is maintained Payroll related changes are logged and paid accordingly Assurance that the company is compliant with all applicable state and federal wage and hour laws for both US and non-US based employees through liaising with external parties and third-party payroll service providers Maintenance of up-to-date Netsuite knowledge with all users being fully trained on navigating the system Job Skills Ability to prepare various journal entries, account reconciliations, and provide general ledger support Ability to work with multiple platforms on non-linear and asymmetric projects, and to perform rapid changes in workflow and process, all in a fast-moving startup tech ecosystem Proven ability to work effectively across departments Effectively communicate with vendors and related parties Ability to grow financial staff by recruiting, selecting, orienting, and training employees Ability to identify internal control weakness and remediations Diligence with respects to disbursements and controls Advanced knowledge of bookkeeping and accounting best practices, laws, standards, and national/international regulations Quick learner, independent, and operate with light management Required Education and Experience Bachelor\u2019s Degree in Accounting or Finance or related field 8+ years of accounting & analytical experience providing actionable information to senior management Experience with Netsuite ERP and general comfort with 3rd party SaaS platforms Experience with payroll process, filing required annual, quarterly, and monthly information reports, and familiarity with SaaS payroll platforms Preferred Education and Experience Actively licensed CPA Expertise with NetSuite ERP and custom report building Benefits and insurance administration Prior experience leading team preferred Strong working knowledge of US GAAP & IFRS WHAT WE OFFER YOU Salary band: $77,000 - $90,000 100% Covered Health, Dental and Vision Insurance Flexible Time Off 401(k) Parking & Commuter Benefits Generous Maternity and Paternity Leave Opportunity to be paid in Bitcoin Required Travel No travel is expected for this position. Other Duties Please note this job description is not designed to cover or contain a comprehensive listing of activities, duties or responsibilities that are required of the employee for this job. Duties, responsibilities and activities may change 